cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the analysis of convolutional neural networks (ConvNets) for visual recognition tasks, specifically object classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of ridge regression, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper's focus on exploiting spatial information in earlier layers of ConvNets suggests that it could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper's use of visual recognition tasks and image descriptors could also make it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
